{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of New Music Research | cover = | editor = Alan Marsden | discipline = | former_names = Interface | abbreviation = J. New Music Res. | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1972-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.122 | impact-year = 2016 | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/aboutThisJournal?journalCode=nnmr20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/nnmr | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/nnmr20 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 681042287 | LCCN = 94649792 | CODEN = JNEMEE | ISSN = 0929-8215 | eISSN = 1744-5027 }} '''''Journal of New Music Research''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering research on [[musicology]] (including [[music theory]]), [[philosophy]], [[psychology]], [[acoustics]], computer science, engineering, and other disciplines. Articles deal with theory, analysis, composition, performance, uses of music, instruments, and other music technologies. The journal was established in 1972 under the title ''Interface'' and is published by [[Routledge]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Alan Marsden ([[Lancaster University]]).
