'''Maria Adelaide Amaral''' (born 1 July 1942, in [[Alfena]]) is a [[Portuguese Brazilian]] playwright, screenwriter, and novelist. A good deal of her plays concern disaffected urban professionals.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=97NoYRx96ZAC&pg=PA307&dq=%22Maria+Adelaide+Amaral%22&hl=en&ei=F89ITqmpLITEsQKqtr2SCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDwQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=%22Maria%20Adelaide%20Amaral%22&f=false The Cambridge history of Latin American literature: Brazilian ..., Volume 2 by Roberto González Echevarrı́a, pg 307]</ref> She has been classed as among the two major women playwrights of Brazil, the other being [[Leilah Assunção]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=w0Lc79wP-40C&pg=PA32 Tentative transgressions: homosexuality, AIDS, and the theater in Brazil by Severino João Medeiros Albuquerque, pg 32]</ref>

In 1994, Maria Adelaide Amaral [[Biography|biographed]] the Brazilian comedian [[Dercy Gonçalves]]. The book was titled ''Dercy de Cabo a Rabo''. In 2012, Amaral adapted this book into the [[miniseries]] ''Dercy de Verdade''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tribunadonorte.com.br/noticia/dercy-de-cabo-a-rabo-em-livro-e-na-teve/207936
|title=Dercy de cabo a rabo em livro e na tevê (in Portuguese)
|publisher=Tribuna do Norte
|date=4 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0,,EMI285170-9531,00-HELOISA+PERISSE+E+FAFY+SIQUEIRA+FALAM+SOBRE+A+MINISSERIE+DERCY+DE+VERDADE.html
|title=Heloisa Perissé e Fafy Siqueira falam sobre a minissérie "Dercy de Verdade" (in Portuguese)
|publisher=Quem magazine
|date=16 December 2011}}</ref>

Despite her work as writer, she is perhaps best known to the public as an author of [[telenovela]]s, including the [[Ti Ti Ti (2010)|2010 remake of ''Ti Ti Ti'']].<ref>[http://tititi.globo.com/Bastidores/noticia/2011/02/maria-adelaide-amaral-visita-estudio-de-ti-ti-ti.html Ti-Ti-Ti page at Rede Globo (In Portuguese)]</ref>

